    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offering an investment-grade FD3S RX-7, preserved in its original factory configuration. This specimen features the legendary 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, exhibiting optimal compression across all rotor faces with no signs of apex seal fatigue. The power delivery is seamless, managed by a precise 5-speed manual gearbox and a factory Torsen limited-slip differential. The chassis remains exceptionally rigid, retaining its signature 50:50 weight distribution and supported by a pristine double-wishbone suspension assembly with all bushings and dampers in factory-spec condition. Cooling system integrity has been verified, and the intricate vacuum line network\u2014the 'rat's nest'\u2014is fully functional and leak-free. The exterior finish and interior appointments are devoid of any UV degradation or tactile wear. This is a rare, unmolested example of 90s longitudinal-engine, rear-drive engineering at its zenith.",
